      • buy

        public static int buy(int type,
                      java.lang.String sym,
                      java.lang.String nam,
                      int quant,
                      double pr)
        Method ask user for input and creates a new stock or mutual fund if one does not already exist.
        Parameters:
        type - investment type (Stock or mutual fund).
        sym - investment symbol.
        nam - investment name.
        quant - investment quantity.
        pr - investment price.
        Returns:
        EXIT_SUCCESS if buying was successful, EXIT_FAILURE otherwise.

      • check

        public static int check(java.lang.String key,
                        int stockOrFund,
                        double pr,
                        int qty)
        Method checks if symbol inputted by user already exists as a stock or mutual fund.
        Parameters:
        key - Symbol to check for uniqueness.
        stockOrFund - String that can either be a stock or mutual fund, used to determine whether to add to existing list or tell user that they made an error.
        pr - investment price.
        qty - investment quantity.
        Returns:
        EXISTS_UPDATED, EXISTS_NOT_UPDATED or DOES_NOT_EXIST based on the search results.

        index - Integer index of investment position in its respective list.
